Privacy Policy for Breeders X App

Effective Date: 11/1/2024

This Privacy Policy explains how BreedEx collects, uses, shares, and protects information in connection with the BreedEx mobile application. By using the App, you agree to the collection and use of information as outlined in this policy.

1. Information We Collect
A. Personal Information
We do not collect personally identifiable information (such as name and email address) unless you voluntarily provide it. Any personal information you choose to provide will be used strictly for account-related purposes within the App.

B. Herd and Cow Data
As part of the App functionality, we collect data that you voluntarily input regarding your herds and cows. This includes, but is not limited to:

Herd data: name, size, etc.
Cow data: age, name, calving times, date of birth (DOB), and additional categories that are relevant to tracking health and productivity.
C. Scoring and Quiz Data
The App includes scoring and quiz features that allow users to assess their herds and individual cows across different categories. We collect scoring data, quiz results, and related metrics solely for the purpose of delivering personalized insights and tracking improvements over time.

D. Usage Data
To improve the App’s functionality, we may collect certain non-personal usage information such as:

App usage data (e.g., interactions within the App, feature usage, time spent, etc.)
Device information (e.g., device type, operating system)
2. How We Use Your Information
We use the data we collect to:

Provide and improve the App’s features and functionality
Store your herd and cow information to enable access and tracking over time
Display quiz scores and other metrics on the App’s user interface for your review and analysis
Analyze user behavior within the App to enhance our services
3. How We Store and Secure Your Information
All data is securely stored on Firebase servers. Firebase employs industry-standard security practices, including encryption, to protect your data. Access to your information is restricted to authorized personnel and is only used as necessary to provide and improve our services.

4. Sharing of Information
We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to outside parties. Information may be shared only under the following conditions:

Legal Requirements: We may disclose information if required by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities.
Business Transfers: If we are involved in a merger, acquisition, or asset sale, your data may be transferred to the new entity, with proper notice and choices provided where necessary.
5. Third-Party Services
We use Firebase, a third-party service provided by Google, for data storage and analytics. Firebase may collect certain data as outlined in their Privacy Policy, which you can review for further details: Firebase Privacy Policy.

6. User Control and Data Retention
You have the right to:

Access: Request access to view the data we hold about you.
Update: Update the herd or cow data as needed within the App.
Delete: Request the deletion of your data by contacting us directly.
Data is retained as long as necessary to provide the App’s services. Upon request or account termination, we will securely delete or anonymize your data as applicable.

7. Children’s Privacy
The Breeders App is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13. If we discover that a child has provided us with personal information, we will take steps to delete such information promptly.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with the updated effective date. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

9. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

ymicattleco@gmail.com
By using the Breeders App, you consent to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
